<item>
            <title>[LU-19426] dynamic nodemap: primary fileset can be set outside parent&apos;s restrictions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19426</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a persistent nodemap has an alternate fileset defined, and a dynamic nodemap is created with that persistent nodemap as a parent, it is able to set a primary fileset outside of the parent&apos;s fileset restrictions with &quot;lctl nodemap_set_fileset&quot;.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected behavior: &quot;lctl nodemap_set_fileset&quot; should stay within the parent&apos;s namespace restrictions defined by its fileset.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
